{
  "title": "Heat Storage 1B: Heat storage depends on specific heat",
  "publicationStatus": "public",
  "subtitle": "Why do some materials take longer to heat up or cool down than others?",
  "about": [
    "How much heat is stored in an object depends on its specific heat, as described by the formula below:",
    "",
    "*Q* = **c**p⋅**m**(*T*final-*T*initial)",
    "",
    "This model is similar to 1A, except that the specific heats of the two rectangular objects are different.",
    "",
    "1.  Run the model and note the temperatures measured by the two thermometers.",
    "2.  Wait until the temperatures of the two objects do not change any further.",
    "3.  Note the final temperature of the two objects.",
    "",
    "Reset the model and change the specific heats of the two",
    "objects using the sliders below the model. Repeat steps 1-3 for",
    "two more different setups. Make sure that the specific heats are",
    "different in each setup."
  ],
  "importedFrom": "imports/energy2d/content-htb/S1B.html",
  "models": [
    {
      "type": "energy2d",
      "id": "S1B1",
      "url": "imports/energy2d/models-json/S1B1.json",
      "importedFrom": "imports/energy2d/models-xml/S1B1.e2d",
      "viewOptions": {
        "controlButtons": "play_reset"
      }
    }
  ],
  "parameters": [
    {
      "name": "left-block",
      "label": "Left block specific heat",
      "unitAbbreviation": "kg⋅°C",
      "onChange": "getPart(0).specific_heat = value;",
      "initialValue": 1000
    },
    {
      "name": "right-block",
      "label": "Right block specific heat",
      "unitAbbreviation": "kg⋅°C",
      "onChange": "getPart(1).specific_heat = value;",
      "initialValue": 2000
    }
  ],
  "components": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "specific-heat-label",
      "text": "### Specific heat (kg⋅°C):"
    },
    {
      "type": "slider",
      "id": "left-block-slider",
      "property": "left-block",
      "title": "Left block",
      "min": 100,
      "max": 5000,
      "displayValue": "return format('.1f')(value)",
      "labels": [
        {
          "value": 100,
          "label": "100"
        },
        {
          "value": 5000,
          "label": "5000"
        }
      ],
      "steps": 49,
      "width": "10em"
    },
    {
      "type": "slider",
      "id": "right-block-slider",
      "property": "right-block",
      "title": "Right block",
      "min": 100,
      "max": 5000,
      "displayValue": "return format('.1f')(value)",
      "labels": [
        {
          "value": 100,
          "label": "100"
        },
        {
          "value": 5000,
          "label": "5000"
        }
      ],
      "steps": 49,
      "width": "10em"
    },
    {
      "type": "graph",
      "id": "graph",
      "title": "Temperature Probes: T1, T2",
      "xlabel": "Time (s)",
      "ylabel": "Temperature (°C)",
      "ymin": 0,
      "ymax": 50,
      "xmax": 300,
      "xTickCount": 5,
      "xFormatter": ".2s",
      "yFormatter": ".2s",
      "xProperty": "time",
      "properties": [
        "sensor-1", "sensor-0"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "layout": {
    "bottom": [
      "specific-heat-label", "left-block-slider", "right-block-slider"
    ],
    "right": [ "graph" ]
  },
  "template": "wide-right"
}